 -- Hermann Vosseler <deb@ichthyostega.de>  Mon, 02 Nov 2015 23:11:07 +0100

lumiera (0.pre.02-1+jessie) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * adjustments to build Lumiera for Debian/Jessie
    * use Clang for building, since gcc-48 has a regression
      in the TR1 implementation of the ref() function
    * disable the priority queue test, which causes frequent
      failures in package buidling due to excessive load

 -- Hermann Vosseler <deb@ichthyostega.de>  Fri, 15 Nov 2013 05:43:23 +0100

lumiera (0.pre.02-1) Lumiera-wheezy; urgency=low

  * [c848903] new upstream (pre Alpha)release 0.pre.02
  * all gcc-4.7 and clang-3 compatibility fixes are on master now
  * compatibility for boost/filesystem 2->3 transition
  * remove all preliminary fixes done for building on various distros
  * update git-buildpackage config to pick the upstream tag automatically
  * clean *.pcy and optcache prior to packaging
  * build with -fstack-protector --param=ssp-buffer-size=4
  * enable using all available CPU cores for build
  * fix some 32/64bit problems found while packaging

 -- Hermann Vosseler <deb@ichthyostega.de>  Sun, 10 Nov 2013 23:03:23 +0100

